        About this item

        • 2023 Upgraded Walking Pad--The stronger steel frame structure ensures your safety while exercising, and the oil drip hole in the upper right corner allows you to refuel the motor, making the running belt smoother during work and bringing you a better running experience.
        • Portable & Compact Design--DeerRun mini under desk treadmill is designed to be a super space-saving walking machine for home office workout as this walking pad weighs only 41.8 pounds and has a small size of only 44*20*4.5 inches, with the built-in wheels you can easily stored the walking pad under the office desk, bed or sofa.
        • Powerful & Quiet Motor--The 2.5HP motor enables our treadmill to provide a speed of 0.6~3.8 and a maximum capacity of 265 pounds, while keeping the noise below 50 decibels. Provides a smooth and near-silent workout experience, ideal for both work and leisure.
        • 5-layers 16" Running Belt--This home treadmill walking pad uses a 16" wider 5-layer anti-slip belt and silicone posts to support the impact you experience while exercising, providing protection for your knees, muscles and joints.
        • Professional Customer Service--DeerRun under desk treadmill comes with a 12-month warranty, whether you encounter any problems before or after sales, you can contact us at any time, our professional customer team provides you with email and phone service.

        Product Description

        Walking Pad is an easy and effective way to stay active and improve your health, but sometimes the weather or your schedule doesn't allow for it. A solution to this problem is a DeeRun desk walking pad, its versatility allows you to use it almost anywhere.

        • Multi-speed & LED display: Easily adjust the speed of the treadmill by using the remote control, and the walking pad's LED display allows you to view distance, time, calories and speed in real time. With a speed range of 0.6-3.8 MPH, you can customize your workout to suit your needs.
        • 2.5 Powerful Motor: The 2.5 horsepower DeerRun walking mat treadmill can hold up to 265 pounds and run at less than 50 decibels. Use this under desk treadmill while answering the phone, the person you're talking to won't hear noisy background sounds.
        • Space-saving & Compact Design: Our portable mini treadmill is designed to fit into any space. The desk treadmill is only 4.5 inches thick and won't take up much space in your home. The ultra-slim design and built-in wheels make the walking pad easy to store under your desk, bed, or sofa.
        • Ultra-lightweight & Portable Treadmill: This under desk walking treadmill is compact in design, with a body size of 44 x 20 inches and a body weight of only 41.8 pounds, both men and women can easily lift this walking machine.
        • Weight Loss: This DeerRun walking pad allows you to burn calories and lose weight. You can walk or run at a steady pace, which can help you burn more calories than you would if you were walking outside.

        In conclusion, a walking pad is a great piece of exercise equipment that offers many benefits. Whether you're looking to lose weight, improve your cardiovascular health, or reduce stress, a desk treadmill for office or home can help you achieve your goals.

            How customer reviews and ratings work

            Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

            To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

            Palebluedot
            4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent, but..
            Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
            Color: 1-BlackVerified Purchase
            This walking pad is extremely convenient. It has allowed me to walk consistently everyday because I dont have to go to the basement gym and be away from my family. It lives in the living room and is easily stowed away under the couch within minutes. Its quite as can be, considering its a machine with a major moving part (the belt).
            Pluses:
            1) its quiet. I received a loud one at first, I returned it and got a replacement and it has been great.
            2) its moveable. This is a sturdy machine. It has to be or it cant support your moving weight. However, the casters at the bottom on one side (for safety) allow it to be moved and slide under furniture with ease.
            3) unlike some other ones, this particular model shows distance in miles, not kilometers. Thats a plus for us Americans. We dont have to convert our mileage.
            4) trouble shooting is simple. If the belt is bearing left while you walk, you just crank it with the provided wrench and it immediately corrects itself. If you do too much, you just adjust the other side. It took me 5 seconds to do it and it hasnt gotten misaligned again. Ive done 75 miles on it after.

            Cons:
            1) its narrow. But thats by design. Its meant to be narrow so that its portable. This isnt a full sized treadmill so dont expect it to be. That also means that you must pay attention. If you are not centered, you WILL fall. I did - twice. Instead of returning it and getting a model that has handle bars, I just put two chair backs on either side and use them to keep my balance.
            That works for me but it is a compromise and if I had it in me to return it, I would pick the handle bar model. But I do have bad balance to begin with. So use your judgment.
            2) it does NOT keep time. If you accidentally press stop, it will stop withOUT a recorded time or distance. So if youre keeping track of your progress, you wont know how many calories, distance, or time. I find this one the most annoying of the flaws. I make it a point to glance at my time and distance BEFORE I end my session.
            3) you must use the remote to stop, start, increase or decrease the speed. The remote has a loose wrist band so I wear it on my wrist while I walk. You can also thread it through a lanyard to keep it hands free.
            4) it does not have an emergency stop button to pull.

            All in all, I recommend this walking pad for this price point. I would probably have gotten a different model for my specific needs, but as it stands, Im happy keeping this one.
